President Trump and Secretary of Transportation Elaine Chao honored truck drivers for their crucial role in the fight against the coronavirus pandemic. They praised truckers for delivering supplies that American families need and keeping the economy running. The administration has taken steps to support truckers, such as easing regulations and ensuring truck stops remain open. Truck drivers from companies like UPS, DHL Express, and FedEx Ground shared their experiences and were presented with ceremonial keys as a token of appreciation. President Trump also mentioned plans for an infrastructure package and urged support from Democrats.